Clinicians must remain watchful to distinguish viral laryngitis with differential diagnoses of diseases that can present with stridor and respiratory distress (Box 25-1
). Bacterial causes should be suspected in children with severe respiratory distress and toxic appearance.Box 25-1Diagnoses to be Considered in Children with Stridor and Respiratory Distress
•Croup•Epiglottitis•Bacterial tracheitis•Laryngeal diphtheria•Tracheal foreign-body aspiration•Retropharyngeal abscess•Peritonsillar abscess•Angioneurotic edema•Allergic reaction and anaphylaxis
